# C++ Style Conventions

## Naming

- **Types/classes**: PascalCase, full words — `ExpressionCodeGenerator`, not `ExprCodeGen`
- **Methods/variables**: camelCase, full words — `generator`, not `gen`; `expression`, not `expr`
- **Constants**: `kCamelCase` — `kCommentCpp20ColumnAliases`
- **No single-letter variables** — use descriptive names
- **No abbreviations** in names unless universally understood (e.g. `id`, `url`)

## Fields and `this->`

- **No underscore suffixes** on member fields — write `generator`, not `generator_` or `gen_`
- **Always use `this->`** to access member fields — `this->generator`, `this->columnTypes`

```cpp
// BAD
CodeGenerator& gen_;
this->gen_.generateNode(node);

// GOOD
CodeGenerator& generator;
this->generator.generateNode(node);
```

## General

- C++20, 4-space indentation
- `#pragma once` for header guards
- `struct` for data/POD types, `class` for types with logic
- `operator==` via `= default` where possible
- Everything inside `namespace sqlite2orm { }`, indented one level
- Anonymous `namespace { }` for file-internal helpers (not `static`)
- Include order: project headers (`<sqlite2orm/...>`), then STL
